article.headline: Delaware St. 66, Howard 57
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Jahsha Bluntt had 18 points, six rebounds and blocked two shots to lead Delaware State to a 66-57 win against Howard on Saturday. Delaware State (7-9, 4-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) had four players score in double digits. Troy Roundtree and Roy Bright scored 12 points each. Darrin Shine scored 10 points. Howard (6-11, 2-3) was led by Will Gant, who scored 16 points. Darryl Hudson scored 13. Jason Trotter led Howard in rebounds with 10. Howard struggled at the free-throw line, making only 6-of-15. Delaware State fared much better at free throws, making 13-of-17. Bluntt went 6-of-9 in field goals and 1-of-3 in 3-point shots. He was 5-of-5 from the free-throw line. Delaware State lead at halftime 40-31. Delaware State opened up a 46-35 lead on a Roundtree lay up with 15:35 left to play. Howard answered with a 14-6 run, and pulled to within 52-49 after a 3-point shot by Darek Mitchell with 7:50 remaining. Delaware State led 56-52 before pulling away for good. The win was the Hornets eighth win in a row against the Bison.
